<collectingCountry box="[1029,1114,1614,1640]" name="Mexico" pageId="9" pageNumber="290">Mexico</collectingCountry>
border in the northern GOM, NMFS SEFSC trawl surveys have captured this species as far south as southern Florida, at the approximate level of Everglades City, Florida. This species has been reported from depths of 
<quantity box="[958,1096,1685,1713]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.225" metricValueMax="5.9" metricValueMin="0.55" pageId="9" pageNumber="290" unit="m" value="322.5" valueMax="590.0" valueMin="55.0">
55 to 
<specimenCount box="[1022,1096,1685,1713]" pageId="9" pageNumber="290" type="generic">590 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
