<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="290" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1613,2037]" pageId="9" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1866,1892]" pageId="9" pageNumber="290">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was considered by 
<bibRefCitation author="McEachran, J. D." box="[681,892,1866,1892]" pageId="9" pageNumber="290" pagination="423 - 439" refId="ref18931" refString="McEachran, J. D. (1977) Variation in Raja garmani and the status of Raja lentiginosa (Pisces: Rajidae). Bulletin of Marine Science, 27 (3), 423 - 439." type="journal article" year="1977">McEachran (1977)</bibRefCitation>
to be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1939" box="[1138,1293,1867,1892]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Rajidae" genus="Raja" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rajiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="290" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="garmani">
<emphasis box="[1138,1293,1867,1892]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="290">Raja garmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="McEachran, J. D. &amp; Dunn, K. A." pageId="9" pageNumber="290" pagination="271 - 290" refId="ref19026" refString="McEachran, J. D. &amp; Dunn, K. A. (1998) Phylogenetic analysis of skates, a morphologically conservative clade of elasmobranches (Chondrichthyes: Rajidae). Copeia, 1998 (2), 271 - 290. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1447424" type="journal article" year="1998">McEachran and Dunn (1998)</bibRefCitation>
elevated the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Malm, 1877" authorityName="Malm" authorityYear="1877" box="[624,891,1902,1928]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Rajidae" genus="Leucoraja" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rajiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="290" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[624,739,1903,1928]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="290">Leucoraja</emphasis>
Malm, 1877
</taxonomicName>
to the level of genus and separated 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bigelow and Schroeder" baseAuthorityYear="1951" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Rajidae" genus="Leucoraja" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rajiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="290" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lentiginosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="290">Leucoraja lentiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Whitley" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[347,565,1939,1964]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Rajidae" genus="Leucoraja" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rajiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="290" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="garmani">
<emphasis box="[347,565,1939,1964]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="290">Leucoraja garmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This separation has recently been supported by molecular work (G. Naylor, personal communication).
</paragraph>
